This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category as it discusses the implementation of a neural network hardware architecture on an FPGA platform. It also relates to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it mentions the use of FPGAs in AI and machine learning fields. Additionally, cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories as the paper discusses the use of FPGAs in data sampling and processing industries and autonomous driving. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the implementation of neural networks on an FPGA platform.
